@node big "What are the differences between demo and final version ??"
If  you  obtain the registerized version of the package, you'll will
receive a version with no restrictions left in it !  The loading and
saving  of  preferences  is enabled, and the program will try to get
your  favourite  preferences from the ENVARC:  directory on startup.
@endnode

@node keys "The magic is below your hands ..."
DePack!   is  controlled  by  keyboard  with  support  of  intuition
elements  like  menus  or file-requesters.  Here is how the keys are
assigned :

	Return/Enter	-	Mark Entry below cursor
	Cursor Up	-	Move cursor one line up
	Cursor Down	-	Move cursor one line down
	Numeric CrsrUp	-	Move cursor one line up
	Numeric CrsrDw	-	Move cursor one line down (u guessed it!)
	Shift+CrsrUp	-	Move cursor one page up
	Shift+CrsrDw	-	Move cursor one page down
	Shift+NumCrsrUp	-	Move cursor one page up
	Shift+NumCrsrDw	-	Move cursor one page down
	Numeric Home	-	Move cursor to line #1
	Numeric	End	-	Move cursor to last line
	Numeric PgUp	-	Move cursor one page up
	Numeric PgDw	-	Move cursor one page down
@endnode


@node tech "Technical information"
This  chapter  of  the  manuals  provides  information for all those
freaks out there who want to know about the coder-side of DePack!

DePack!   opens a public screen (name :  'DePack!'), so you can open
any other program with public screen support on DePack!'s screen.

DePack!   in  todays  form was developed in 8 months of more or less
intensive work (4 months of intensive work, 3 were lazy business) on
a  Amiga  500  with  a  52MB  harddisk  and  4  MB  of  memory (well
unaccelerated  ;).   The  sourcecode  is split into 15 modules to be
linked  after  compilation (See list below).  By the way ...  if you
order the full DePack!-package you will get the complete sourcecode.



	    Below are some charts for your information :


DePack! sourcecode-length (The following is a LIST-ing of the dir) :

ReadDir.c                  12759 ----rwed Today     19:30:48
Render.c                    7781 ----rwed Monday    23:28:00
Keys.c                      3492 ----rwed 02-Nov-93 21:35:30
StatusWindow.c             13502 ----rwed Today     01:22:58
Prefs.c                     2619 ----rwed Yesterday 21:28:10
Amigaguide.c                1140 ----rwed 03-Nov-93 22:28:40
