Reqs.c                     13528 ----rwed Today     23:26:30
15 files - 208 blocks used (approx 100K)
@endnode

@node dirfilestruct "The inner core"
Depack!   uses  several layout conventions of the dirfile which must
be obeyed if you load files for use as Depack!-directory-files.

· The maximum line length is limited to 100 characters.
· The maximum amount of total lines is limited to 32000

The dirfile is a textfile with the following structure :

	Entry 1
	Entry 2
	  ·
	  ·
	  ·
	Entry n			( 0 < n < 32000)




An entry is defined as :

	Startline
	Descriptionline 1
	Descriptionline 2
	  ·
	  ·
	  ·
	Descriptionline n	(Desciptionlines optional 0 < n < 8)



Startline :

XXXXXXXXXXX ..............................................................

filename    (rest of line not referenced)
(up to 30 chars)




Descriptionline :
 .........................................................................

First character must be <Space> or <Tab> ! The rest is not referenced.




Example :
---------

PARTY93.DMS  P 110835  09-01-93  ·+­­­­­­!­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­+·
                                  |  _  _:____  ________________/\ [Hb]| 
                                  |      ˇ\ __\/_/ / __/_  / __/  \    | 
                                  |    _  _\ \/ / /___/ / / /\/ /\/    | 
                                  |     _/___/ /\__/_/\_\_\/\  /       | 
                                  |          \/              \/        | 
                                 ·+­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­­+·
                                  `   INVITATION  FOR  THE PARTY III   '
is a valid entry.

its_sm.dms                645771 ----rwed 05-Oct-93 17:27:25
jhh.lc!.txt                43613 ----rwed 05-Oct-93 17:55:48
JSM-NBA1.DMS              710036 ----rwed 17-Oct-93 22:16:59
JSM-NBA2.DMS              751952 ----rwed 17-Oct-93 22:10:33
JSM-NBA3.DMS              688716 ----rwed 17-Oct-93 22:09:42
JSM-NWBL.DMS              569952 ----rwed 17-Oct-93 22:32:21

is also valid. This is the output of a 'list' command


S_ST3.1.DMS  P 390871  09-01-93     __________ ______ ______ ________________
                                  _/  _____ I \\__ _ \\____ \\__ _____  ____/
                                  \___  \/     \/ _j  \/  |  \/  _>__\___  \ 
                                  /  !   \  T   \ l_   \  !   \  !~ \~  !   \
GREATPROGRAM                     /    ___/__l___/__l___/______/_____/___    /
                                 \____j-----------------------------sctl___/
                                      SHADESTRACKER 3.1 - LATEST UPDATE
                                                                   [-SlAyER-]

is  not  valid because the string "GREATPROGRAM" at the beginning of
the  5th  is  no  filename and deserves a <Space> or <Tab> appearing
before to belong to the description.

A  dirfile  can  contain  many subsequent entries.  If you select an
item  by  pressing  <Return> or <Enter> anywhere between the 1st and
8th line of an entry it will get marked !
@endnode



@node about "About DePack!"
DePack! is an easy to use tool for /X sysops and traders who like to
DePack! their software stored and cramped into packed files produced
by archivers like 'lha', 'zoo', diskmashed with 'dms' or simply read
the newest textfiles available in their BBS-directories.

The  basic  idea  is  that  you  select a couple of files from an /X
directory  simply  by  marking  them  with a cursor and then perform
certain  operations  e.g.   copy  them to an other directory, delete
them  or  (and  that is the main thing behind DePack!) call external
commands  (in  form  of  AmigaDos executables) depending on the file
type.   This  means that e.g.  if you select an DiskMasher-file, you
are  asked to enter a disk and then the 'dms'-command will be called
externally  and  the  data stored in the .dms-file will be written a
disk  in  df0:.   If  the  file  is  a IFF-ILBM file you can call an
external viewer and display the picture stored in the file.

This  whole  idea was born by some member(s) of the group 'D-TECT' a
long  time  ago.  They released 'D-Tect's Deluxe DePacker', but this
programm was so badly written (assembler hardcode) with so many bugs
and  a  bad GUI that I decided to reprogram the whole thing with the
following goals in my mind :  a) Written in C (as I started coding C
last  year)  b)  High-Quality  Graphical  User Interface c) Enhanced
functions and features.

I tried to obey all the rules given in the Commodore Style Guide (as
far  as  I know them ...  I ordered the book 1 year ago, and I still
wait for it !)
@endnode

@node install "Installing DePack!"
To  install  DePack!   double click the Icon 'DePack!-Install'.  You
must   have   the   commodore   installer  tool  installed  in  your
c:-directory.   All  files  needed  will  be  copied to the path you
specify.

See Also : 
@{" Requirements " link requirements}
@endnode

@node requirements "Requirements"
DePack!   needs  some  additional  files  to  work, some of them are
essential to start the program, some of them are optional :

Required things :

- OperatingSystem 2.0 or higher (starting with V37)
			- for the GadTools.library GUI

- diskfont.library (V37 or higher)
			- for the output routines

- reqtools.library (V38 or higher)
			- for the requesters


Optional things :

- amigaguide.library (any version will do)
			- for using the hypertext-help system

- fonts:p0t-noodle.font
  fonts:p0t-noodle/8
			- this is the default DePack! font, if it doesn't
			  find it it will switch to use the topaz/8 ROM-font
@endnode

@node starterrors "Error's while starting DePack!"
When  trying  to  start DePack, it probably prints out several error
codes  if  it  has  some  problems  while  finding free libraries or
memories.   Look  into  the list below how to find and fix the error
codes.

	@{" Error  1 " link error1}  Error opening disk libraries
	@{" Error  2 " link error2}  Error opening ROM libraries
	@{" Error  3 " link error3}  Error opening screen
	@{" Error  4 " link error4}  Error opening window
@endnode

@node error1 "Error 1 while starting DePack!"
DePack!   had  problems opening the required libraries.  Perhaps you
need a newer version of a library or the library is not installed in
the libs:  drawer

	Libraries Required		Versions Required

	diskfont.library		>=V37
	reqtools.library		>=V38
@endnode

@node error2 "Error 2 while starting DePack!"
DePack!   had  problems opening the required ROM libraries.  Perhaps
you  have  a wrong kickstart (V1.3 or lower).  DePack!  only runs on
V2.0 or a newer version of the operating system :

	Libraries Required		Versions Required

	gadtools.library		>=V37
	intuition.library		>=V37
	gfx.library			>=V37
@endnode

@node error3 "Error 3 opening screen"
DePack!  had problems opening the screen.  Perhaps you have too less
chip memory free.
@endnode

@node error4 "Error 4 opening window"
DePack!  had problems opening the window.  Perhaps you have too less
chip memory free.
@endnode

